The Rwandan authorities have introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus, including suspending all flights to and from Kigali International Airport from 23:59 local time on 20 March, for an initial period of 30 days.
You should urgently contact your airline or tour operator if you are due to travel to or from Rwanda. The closure of borders and restrictions on movement outside of residences, including travel between cities and districts, was introduced at 23.59 on 21 March for two weeks.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
